<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="Tutorial_SP46_HomeChefHustles_StreetFoodTable" s="338121">
  <T n="category">338300<!--tutorial_Category_HomeChefHustles--></T>
  <T n="name">0x4E29EE31<!--Food Stand--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InSP46\UI\Tutorial\HomeChefHustles_StreetFoodTable_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:c23579a5927571a6</T>
      <T n="text">0x62C454B9<!--Bring your home chef hustle dreams to life with the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Food Stand</font></b>!\n\nUse it to <b><font color='#199C2C'>sell</font></b> food and other items from the comfort of your Sim's home, or put it in your <b><font color='#199C2C'>inventory</font></b> and bring their booming business around the world.\n\nThe handy dandy side tables allow you to cook with <b><font color='#199C2C'>small appliances</font></b> on the go!\n--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InSP46\UI\Tutorial\HomeChefHustles_StreetFoodTable_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:c23579a5927571a5</T>
      <T n="text">0x477C64AA<!--To prepare a sale, <b><font color='#199C2C'>drag</font></b> food or other items to the Food Stand or its inventory. When you’re ready, choose <b><font color='#199C2C'>Start Food Sale</font></b>, and customers will flock to your table!\n\nYour Sim will automatically <b><font color='#199C2C'>stock</font></b> the table when the sale starts, and keep restocking it over time as things get sold. You can select Disable AutoStock to stock manually instead.\n\nIf your Sim has to take a break, they can continue selling by selecting <b><font color='#199C2C'>Tend Table</font></b>.\n\nThe Street Food Sale will end when the timer runs out.\n--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InSP46\UI\Tutorial\HomeChefHustles_StreetFoodTable_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:c23579a5927571a4</T>
      <T n="text">0xA7CAF3F8<!--Increasing the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Mark Up</font></b> will earn you more Simoleons per sale, but it will also make customers less likely to buy something.\n\nYour Sim can attempt to <b><font color='#199C2C'>Give Sales Pitch</font></b> to make a customer more interested in your wares.\n\nSelect <b><font color='#199C2C'>Convince to Buy</font></b> to try and sell a specific item to a customer! Convince them to buy your most expensive dish, or something... <i>special</i> if your Sim is feeling mischievous.\n\nImproving your Sim’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>Charisma</font></b> skill and completing the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Market Magnate</font></b> aspiration will make them better at selling items, Give Sales Pitch, and Convince To Buy.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InSP46\UI\Tutorial\HomeChefHustles_StreetFoodTable_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:c23579a5927571a3</T>
      <T n="text">0x8E2F7117<!--To place a <b><font color='#199C2C'>small appliance</font></b> on the Food Stand, you can either purchase or move it in Build Mode, drag it onto the table in Live Mode, or select <b><font color='#199C2C'>Place Appliance</font></b> to place it from your Sim’s Inventory.\n\nMost small appliances allow your Sim to cook while they’re still tending the table. How efficient!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InSP46\UI\Tutorial\HomeChefHustles_StreetFoodTable_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:c23579a5927571a2</T>
      <T n="text">0xA88FEADE<!--Take your business on the road by bringing the Food Stand, appliances, and wares in your Sim’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>inventory</font></b> when they travel.\n\nPick up the Food Stand by selecting <b><font color='#199C2C'>Put in Inventory</font></b>, find your new location, and select <b><font color='#199C2C'>Place In World</font></b> on the table in the inventory. You can also <b><font color='#199C2C'>drag</font></b> the table in and out of your Sim’s inventory while it’s on a lot.\n\nIf the Food Stand has wares or appliances on it, your Sim needs to <b><font color='#199C2C'>Clear Table</font></b> before they can pick it up.--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
